<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297619>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Chimarra (Chimarrita) singularis sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, dorsal habitus. 2B, head, right lateral. 2C1, right forewing venation, dorsal. 2C2, right hind wing venation, dorsal. 2D, genitalia, right lateral. 2E, segment IX and tergum X, dorsal. 2F1–2F2, left inferior appendage: 2F1, ventral; 2F2, dorsal. 2G, phallic apparatus, left lateral. Scale bars in mm: 2A = 1; 2B = 0.2; 2C1–2C2 = 0.5; 2D–2G = 0.1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5297619/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297617>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Location of the Campos Amazônicos National Park (CANP), northern Brazil containing collection sites and general views of some of the sampled streams and rivers. 1A, map of the CANP with circles indicating the collection sites. 1B– 1F, general views of sampled waterways: 1B, Branco river (Pt 02); 1C, Jatuarana River (Pt 07); 1D, confluence of Veado Stream with Macaco river (Pt 05); 1E, Veado Stream (Pt 03); 1F, confluence of Macaco and Branco Rivers (Pt 08)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5297617/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

